data.title: Pancakes are a 10!
data.text:
We have been going to Julian's for breakfast for years and I don't know why, but I've never gotten the pancakes, now that makes me sad! 
On the menu they call them "fluffy pancakes" and they were probably some of the best pancakes I've ever had! Honestly a 10! I ordered 2 with a side of bacon, the bacon was really crispy too!!
My husband had the omelet and was happy with his choice. 
It's not very big and there is limited on street parking so if you avoid prime times you should have any issues. 
The staff was pleasant and our service was good. If you are looking for someplace new to try, check it out!

data.title: Wonderful breakfast
data.text:
I had never been here, but was looking forward to a New England Breakfast (includes baked beans).

There were 6 of us and we had a combination of omelletes, eggs, breakfast meats, toast.
I will focus on the delicious meal that I had.

I ordered the Keilbasa Special.

It included:

Grilled Kielbasa (tremendous)
3 Eggs, which I had srcambled
Baked Beans (wonderful)
It came with Brown Bread, but I was able to upgrade to a Corn Muffin, which I had grilled as well.

Everything was perfect. The Corn muffin could not have tasted better. The Kielbasa was grilled and was also as tasty as possible.

The place has charm and there is street parking all around.

data.title: Great neighborhood destination.
data.text: Needed a great place to take visitors from CA. This was such a great choice. Easy to have a conversation with great fare.

data.title: Fabulous, friendly waitress!!
data.text: What they might lack in the food dept., they certainly make up with the super welcoming and friendly service! Food was a mixed bag. The good: sausage patty, baked beans, homefries- all delish. The no-so-good: over cooked eggs, glutinous hollandaise sauce from a pack of powder. Overall tho, a very pleasant experience with food that was fine but not special.

data.title: Lage Portions, Great Service, Cozy Country Atmosphere
data.text:
Went to Julien's County Kitchen for the first time on Sunday, January 31, 2016.  Place was packed, service was great and portions were large ( food was over flowing on plate).
I had scrambled eggs with swiss cheese, hash browns and bacon. I will be back

data.title: New go-to Breakfast Spot!
data.text: After my go-to spot closed on the west side I wanted to give Julien's a shot. So glad I did!!! Very cozy and bright interior with very friendly and attentive service. I tried a chili omelet and my boyfriend tried a kielbasa special with eggs and beans. We were both very pleased with our meals. My friend got the Julien's house special and she loved her meal as well. Food was fresh and tasty, very comfortable atmosphere and great customer service. I will be back for that chili! I would definitely recommend this place as a good option to the pricier places downtown on Elm!

data.title: Downtown Eatery at it's Best
data.text: This restaurant is a real charmer. Breakfast is delicious and made with Fresh ingredients just like mom would make. Owner walks around to say hello to new and old customers. Nice décor. Very eclectic.

data.title: Tasty food, kitschy decor, slow service
data.text: Visited here with some locals for breakfast of eggs, etc.  All was good; coffee was excellent and bacon crispy.  Decor is fun, "brocante" style.  Only real downside was that service was abysmally slow, expecially to get the check.  The locals did say that the delay was unusual, however.

data.title: Meeting place for lunch or breakfast
data.text: How perfect -a small corner street restaurant!   Julien's is a perfect place to meet for lunch or breakfast.   Absolutely the best blueberry pancakes - a New York omelette to die for- many specials to choose from.    Great decor- One sunday morning the place was packed and to my left in the middle table sat Julianne Moore with her daughter and husband on their way to bring their daughter to summer camp!   Always friendly and early morning best on weekends before the rush!  Definitely a place to try!

data.title: One of our best breakfast's ever!
data.text: Fantastic food and great service- perfect combo!  I had the corn beef has breakfast (I think it's called the Irish Breakfast) and it was perfect!  We highly recommend it!

data.title: Food is alright but service is SLOW
data.text: Bring a book or your e reader and hope the weather is nice because you will wait forever to get fed after waiting outside forever to get seated. Very expensive for eggs, toast, and coffee.Steer clear!

data.title: Small and Quiet Place
data.text: Stopped in for lunch with a co-worker.  This is a small quiet restaurant, made to feel very inviting and homey.  Service was great, food was good but not great.  I had the open faced roast turkey, which I saw the cook put in the microwave.  It was a good value and the food was good.

data.title: A chain it is NOT.
data.text: You get a lot for you money at Julien's corner. The first is very warm and welcoming atmosphere. The second is an interesting menu with very tasty food.The third is great service. All of this comes at a very modest cost.

data.title: Homely, friendly and Very Good
data.text:
Tried for breakfast and found the menu and specials offered us plenty of choices to set us up for the day.

An omelette with tomato and onion was very good as was a cinnamon French toast with banana and strawberries. Separate sides of fruit salad were fresh if unexciting. 

But the warm welcome and attentive coffee refills was great

Would return if traveling the same way again

Overall, a rating of Very Good

data.title: Excellent meal and value!
data.text: I had an incredible lunch. I had a Prime Rib Sandwich that was griddled on rye bread with grilled onions and melted provolone cheese. Talk about steak and cheese and taking it up a notch! To top it off, it is served with choice of side. I had the Split Pea soup with Ham. Wow -- what a value! Cute decor and vey attentive service make this little restaurant a real find.

data.title: Great homestyle cooking
data.text: Julien's offers great value and yummy comfort food for breakfast and lunch.  The atmosphere is laid back and welcoming.  Fun nostalgic knickknacks add to the homestyle atmosphere.

data.title: Great service and even better food!
data.text: This is one of those great little places that you just hope to find when traveling in a new city.  Great service and even better food than I had hoped for.  Everything about this little place was spot on.  The staff gets you in and out without making you feel rushed, and makes sure that your cup of coffee doesn't run out or get cold.  They have a great selection of breakfast fare and have a great variety for those that love vegies with their breakfast.  I will back here again, it's worth the trip.

data.title: Big Food & Flavor in a Small Space
data.text:
Very small place,but, worth it!
Get the breakfast special which serves up enough food for a small army!
Well worth it for a couple from far out of town to use a GPS to find the place.
Glad that we did.

data.title: Kind of a being on vacation feel
data.text:
I like diners where the working class is either stoking up for the day or winding down from a shift. This is not that place. This is the cutesy place the ladies go to when they are on vacation and ditched the kids somewhere else. 
As other reviewers said, its small. There are about five tables that really only accommodate two people, then five seats along a window counter. Not really the place for a family of four. When I was there for breakfast there were three retired couples and one single man. Everyone looked like they had nothing better to do in the world. 
There was one waitress. She did a good job keeping everyone happy. She kept the coffee coming, it was not great, but not bad. I ordered the pancakes. It took awhile because I was told they needed to make a fresh batch of batter. Ok, glad I was there on the day it was fresh. I ordered blueberry, but gee, they must be on the blueberry budget plan, because I think I could count how many there were on two hands.  Pretty sad. The bacon clearly was not a fresh batch. It had that "made sometime in the past week" look and was all dried out. I did not bother to finish my breakfast. Waste of calories. 
I was there at breakfast. Plenty of parking around the park.  
My acquaintances suggested here and Red Arrow, which had a TA review that said "greasy". Beats dried out in my book. Will try that next  time.

data.title: best hash in the city
data.text: Cutest breakfast place in the city. Take pride in there food and you can taste it. A must stop place to eat.
